  Don't write a handler for this event. A handler is assigned internally by the control that created
  the instance.
See Also
  OnScaleModeChange
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.OnScaleModeChange
Summary
  Occurs when the ScaleMode property changes
Description
  Don't write a handler for this event. A handler is assigned internally by the control that created
  the instance.
See Also
  OnChange
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows
Summary
  Indicates the number of pages to display horizontally in the visible part of the control.
Description
  Use Rows to specify how many rows of pages should be displayed in the visible part of the preview
  control (without scrolling). Setting Rows may have no effect, either because ScaleMode prohibits it
  or because the number of Rows and Cols requested exceeds the available page count. 
See Also
  Cols, Scale, ScaleMode
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale
Summary
  Indicates the scaling of the pages in the preview.
Description
  \Read Scale to determine the current scaling of the pages. Set the value of Scale to change the scaling.
  Scale is expressed in percentage.
See Also
  Cols, Rows, ScaleMode
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.ScaleMode
Summary
  Indicates the scale mode to use.
Description
  Use ScaleMode to specify how scaling is performed in the preview control. The setting of ScaleMode
  affects how the preview uses the Cols, Rows and Scale properties.
See Also
  Cols, Rows, Scale
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Shadow
Summary
  Reference to settings affecting the page shadow.
Description
  Use Shadow to access the properties that controls the shadow displayed beneath each page.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.VertSpacing
Summary
  Specifies the vertical distance between pages in the preview.
Description
  Use VertSpacing to specify the number of pixels between the pages in a preview when the
  preview is displaying more than one page. VertSpacing is in pixels.
See Also
  HorzSpacing
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode
<TITLE TJvPreviewScaleMode type>
Summary
  The type used for the <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.ScaleMode, ScaleMode>
  property in TJvPreviewPageOptions.
Description
  TJvPreviewScaleMode describes the available scale modes for a preview control.
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smFullPage
  Display a single page. The page is scaled to fit inside the client area of the control.
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smPageWidth
  Display a page so that its width fills the entire client width of the control.
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smScale
  Use the <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, Scale> property to determine the size of the page(s)
  but also use <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, Cols> and <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, Rows>.
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smAutoScale
  Use the <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, Scale> property to determine the size of the page(s)
  and change <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, Cols> and <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, Rows> if necessary.
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smColsRows
  Display as many pages as specified by <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, Cols> and <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, Rows>
  and change <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, Scale> as necessary.
